explanations.unsupervised learning: The paper discusses Hierarchical Agglomerative Clustering (HAC), which is a type of unsupervised learning technique used to identify outliers in financial time series data without labeled examples.
explanations.clustering: The paper explicitly mentions the use of Hierarchical Agglomerative Clustering (HAC) as a method to detect outliers among high-dimensional time series objects, which is a clustering technique.
